      <body>This code 

@@@
defined?(@abstract_class) &amp;&amp; @abstract_class == true
@@@

Makes abstract_class? return true if and only if @abstract_class value is true.

Also docs says you have to assign true to this value

@@@
# Set this to true if this is an abstract class (see &lt;tt&gt;abstract_class?&lt;/tt&gt;).
attr_accessor :abstract_class
@@@

So you're changing the semantics here and allowing things like abstract_class = &quot;hello&quot; to set the model as an abstract_class</body>
      <body-html>&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;This code&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;defined?(@abstract_class) &amp;amp;&amp;amp; @abstract_class == true&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Makes abstract_class? return true if and only if @abstract_class
value is true.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Also docs says you have to assign true to this value&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;
&lt;code&gt;# Set this to true if this is an abstract class (see &amp;lt;tt&amp;gt;abstract_class?&amp;lt;/tt&amp;gt;).
attr_accessor :abstract_class&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So you're changing the semantics here and allowing things like
abstract_class = &quot;hello&quot; to set the model as an abstract_class&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</body-html>
